      "content": "While landmark legislation was vital, the movement was far from straightforward, and many grassroots efforts operated outside the mainstream. Black communities engaged in local organizing, voter registration drives, and economic boycotts that built the foundation for the larger legal battles. Furthermore, more radical factions pushed for immediate, complete systemic upheaval, believing legislative change alone was insufficient. These varied tactics show a complex, multi-pronged fight for true equality.",
